-italic\">r</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>(M1)(A1)A0</strong></em> if '<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>=</mo></math>' is omitted.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33389616","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.11a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the equation of L, expressing your answer in the form r=a+λb, where λ∈ℝ.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.13—Scalar (dot) product","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.14—Vector equation of line"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}